<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25790</anchor> <rss>anon.199.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.199</addr>  <route>anon.199.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Fixing semidirected <tex>J \subseteq  A</tex> such that <tex>j \sqsubseteq   \bigsqcup {J}</tex>, we must show that <tex>J</tex> is inhabited. This follows from our assumption that <tex>i</tex> is positive becuase <tex>i \sqsubseteq  j \sqsubseteq   \bigsqcup {J}</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25791</anchor> <rss>jms-0029.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-0029</addr>  <route>jms-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Positivity is upward-closed</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>i \sqsubseteq  j</tex> in a <link href="jms-001S.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001S" title="Pointed dcpo">pointed</link> dcpo <tex>A</tex> such that <tex>i</tex> is <link href="jms-001M.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001M" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo">positive</link>; then <tex>j</tex> is <link href="jms-001M.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001M" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo">positive</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
